				\begin{document}$$  infection = (1-protection\_level) \times E \times proximity $$\end{document}infection=(1−protection_level)×E×proximityHere, 0 ≤ Omin ≤ E ≤ Omax ≤ 1; Omin and Omax represent lower and upper limits of the impacts of an infected person’s actions on others respectively.

On the other hand, Eq. (2) calculates the infection value due to the positive effects of actions, i.e., washing hands.
